Debate club is fun, my partner and I lost a matchup, down on our luck, my partner told me: “In our next match, I want you to spread.”

In short, spreading is when you say your opening statement SUPER FAST. The point is so your opponent cannot retain any information. If they cannot get much evidence, their case wont thrive and we can just ask away.

We met with out opponents, when it was my turn to speak, I was LIGHTNING SPEED. The spectators said that their face was priceless, they barley got any information and we won.

snippet.textDisplay: Zach: you dig a hole in the ground, it only has one hole. Me: exactly you dig a hole in the ground, it doesn't come out at the bottom. With a hole in the ground, there is only one hole, because it doesn't come out anywhere else, it ends. A straw has two holes because it enters at one end and exits at another end. If the straw was a tunnel, you would enter one hole and travel and exit through another hole, that is the difference between a tunnel and a cave. A cave has one hole that you must enter and exit by, a tunnel has two ways of leaving, therefore it has two holes.

Seek ye the LORD,

all ye meek of the earth,

who have upheld his justice;

seek righteousness,

seek meekness:

it may be ye

shall be hid

in the day of the LORD'S anger.

(Zephaniah 2:3).

***(Seek The Lord): This is the language of true (REPENTANCE), renewal, and regeneration.

***(You will be hidden): Zephaniah used a play on words with meaning of his own name, "Hidden in the Lord." Even in the midst of the most calamitous judgment scenes, the mercy and grace of the Lord is still available to a (REPENTANT) people.

***(Luke 13:3)<---Jesus)<---I tell you, Nay: but, except ye (REPENT), ye shall all likewise perish.

***(Luke 5:32)<---(Jesus)<---I came not to call the righteous, but sinners to (REPENTANCE).

***(2 Peter 3:9)<---The Lord is not slack concerning his promise, as some men count slackness; but is longsuffering to us-ward, not willing that any should perish, but that all should come to (REPENTANCE).

***(Romans 2:4)<---Or do you disregard the riches of His kindness, tolerance, and patience, not realizing that God's kindness leads you to (REPENTANCE?)

* (REPENTANCE):

(Greek. Metanoia); Strong's #3341; This Greek word is a compound word derived from meta, meaning "after" and suggesting some type of change, and nous, meaning "mind."

Thus the word strictly denotes "a change of mind."

But it also connotes remorse for sin, accompanied by a desire to turn away from one's sin, to God, for salvation.

Both John the Baptist and Jesus began their ministries with a call to repentance. (See Matthew 3:2, 4:17)---A call that many of the social outcasts and "sinners" of that day answered, (See Luke 19:1-10),

but that the religious people rejected. (Luke 11:39-44; 18:9-14).

Holy god this triggered me. I went to an arts high school and majored in communications. Freshman year you had to take a semester of speech and debate. I thought it was dumb but I, as a dork, was good at it. Me and another person who thought the events were stupid, performed Fight Club as a duo interp, and people lost their minds. Two guys, not looking at each other, performing every role in Fight Club, including the fights...

My point is this. High school forensics is useless as an event. But you HAVE DISRESPECTED THE INTELLECTUAL EFFORT IT INSTILLS THAT ULTIMATELY TURNS SMART KIND YOUNG PEOPLE INTO STATESPERSONS. There are rules for God's sake.

Love the channel, cheers.
